Making It Beautiful: Adding Style
The basic version works, but let‚Äôs make it stunning. Here‚Äôs an enhanced version with cards, colors, and interactivity:
```{r}
---
title: "Our Team"
format: 
  html:
    css: styles.css
---

library(yaml)
library(glue)

team_data &lt;- yaml::read_yaml("team_members.yml")

# Function to create styled cards
create_team_card &lt;- function(member) {
  skills &lt;- paste(member$skills, collapse = ", ")

  glue('
  &lt;div class="team-card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="avatar"&gt;{substr(member$name, 1, 1)}&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;h3&gt;{member$name}&lt;/h3&gt;
    &lt;p class="role"&gt;{member$role}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;{member$bio}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;div class="skills"&gt;{skills}&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;a href="mailto:{member$email}"&gt;Contact&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  ')
}

# Render all cards
for (member in team_data$team_members) {
  cat(create_team_card(member))
}
```
Add some CSS styling and you get professional-looking cards with hover effects!

Advanced Pattern: Grouping and Filtering
Want to organize by department? Easy:
```{r}
# Group members by department
departments &lt;- unique(sapply(team_members, function(m) m$department))

for (dept in departments) {
  cat("##", dept, "Team\n\n")

  dept_members &lt;- Filter(function(m) m$department == dept, team_members)

  for (member in dept_members) {
    cat(create_team_card(member))
  }
}
```
Now your page automatically organizes people by department!
